<TITLE> 74 councilors to elect BOA president on Aug 20 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 4 (bdnews24.com) - Seventy-four councilors will elect the next president of Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA) on Aug 20. Chief election commissioner of BOA Gazi Mizanur Rahman Tuesday announced the final voter list of 74 councilors, eligible to exercise their voting right for the single post of BOA president. The hot seat has fallen vacant since Gen (retd) Moeen U Ahmed stepped down recently. Out of the 74 councillors, 40 represents 20 leading national sports federations, two came from Women's Sports Association, and two each from six divisional sports associations -- Dhaka, Chittagong, Rajshahi, Khulna, Sylhet and Barisal. One councilor each came from Bangladesh Cricket Board, Chess Federation, Kabaddi Federation, Special Olympics, National Sports Council, Sports Ministry, Bangladesh Ansar, Police, BDR, Army, Navy, and Air Force Sports Control Board. Army chief Gen M Abdul Mubin named the councilor from Army Sports Control Board. Two councilors came from BOA president's quota (Anjan Chowdhury Pintu and Col (retd) Wali Ullah), four from BOA patron sports minister's quota (Obaidul Quader MP, AHM Mostafa Kamal MP, Badal Roy and Dewan Shafiul Arefin Tutul), while the immediate past BOA president and the incumbent secretary general are also included as councilors. As per the election schedule, nomination forms will be distributed on August 10 (10:00 am-4:00 pm).They must be submitted on August 12 (10:00am-4:00 pm). Scrutiny of nomination papers will be made on August 16 (4:00 pm) while the last date for withdrawal of nomination is August 18 (10:00 am-2:00 pm). The final list of candidates will be published on August 18 at 5:00 pm. Voting takes place between 10:00 am-4:00 pm, the preliminary result of the election will be published on the same day at 6:3
